descript.abstract: EPA's Safe Drinking Water Information System (SDWIS) databases store information about drinking water. The federal version (SDWIS/FED) stores the information EPA needs to monitor approximately 156,000 public water systems.
descript.purpose: Data management plays a critical role in helping states and EPA protect public health. The Safe Drinking Water Information System (SDWIS) federal and state databases contain information submitted by states, EPA regions, and public water systems in conformance with reporting requirements established by the Safe Drinking Water Act (SDWA) and related regulations and guidance.
